review_blob: One of tastier chocolate milk stouts to come by on cask, has some full on sweet flavors, and is dangerously drinkable.

Used to be one of my favorite beers in Mississippi, but a recent tasting showed it lacking is depth. Not as dark as I remember it, and a little too sweet. Still, an original brew in an area without much craft.
Among my favorite beers, this is a refreshing and unusual take on IPAs. Beautifully balanced bouquet of flowers.
Amazing session ale. Full-power complexity for a 3% ale, with all the bitterness and refreshing qualities you could ask of a cask pale.
Beautiful bright red color, full on crunchy texture of hoppy bliss. Tastes like a redwood forest, and entirely lives up to its awesome name.
